FBIS4-21928 "jptot015__l94093" JPRS-TOT-94-015-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 3 April 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA ISRAEL Police Capture Fugitive Kakh Leader Barukh Marzel Police Capture Fugitive Kakh Leader Barukh Marzel TA0304043294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0400 GMT 3 Apr 94 TA0304043294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] Barukh Marzel, who was sought by the police for three weeks, was arrested a short while ago in the settlement of Bney Sever, south of Qiryat Arba'. Our police affairs correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports that detectives from the National Unit for Serious Crimes Investigations, policemen from the Judaea Region, and a Border Police contingent captured Barukh Marzel at his hideout. He is currentlty being interrogated at the Petah Tiqva offices of the Natioanl Unit for Serious Crimes Investigations.
